   <text type="letter">
      <body>
         <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.00790.jpg" type="recto"/>
         <opener>
            <dateline>
               <name type="place">New York<ptr target="loc.00572_n1"/></name>
               <date when="1860-05-17">May 17th</date>
            </dateline>
            <salute>Dear Walt.&#8212;</salute>
         </opener> 
         <p>What the devil is the matter?<ptr target="loc.00570_n8"/> Nothing serious I hope.<ptr target="loc.00572_n2"/>&#8212;It seems mighty queer that I
            cannot succeed in having one word from you.&#8212;I swear I would have thought you would
            be the last man in this world to neglect me.&#8212;But I am afraid.&#8212;</p>
         <p>Lizzie is married!, Johnny is dead! Walt has forgotten.</p>
         <closer rend="right">
            <salute>Such is life,</salute> 
            <salute>Yours,</salute>
            <signed>Fred.</signed>
         </closer>
